fields.Title: BACKYARD / MOTHER OF ALL WALLS
fields.OverrideDialogueCondition: (CheckItem("cindys_brush")  and  CheckItem("fuel_canister_rcm")  and  Variable["TASK.add_even_more_beauty_to_the_wall"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.add_even_more_beauty_to_the_wall_done"] == false)  or  Variable["TASK.add_even_more_beauty_to_the_wall_done"]
fields.Description: Stop everything and direct all attention to that wall -- it's sublime!

fields.Title: You: "Why am I looking at this wall?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Why am I looking at this wall?
fields.tooltip1: In the dimming light, some things become clearer.
fields.tooltip2: Dodge ball, really? You don't even have a ball for that.
fields.tooltip3: You have a keen aesthetic sensibility.
fields.variable5: (CheckEquipped("jacket_fucktheworld")  or  CheckEquipped("jacket_pissflaubert"))  and  (CheckEquipped("pants_jeans")  or  CheckEquipped("pants_jeans_black")  or  CheckEquipped("pants_itchy_angry"))

fields.Title: You: "Yes, I must paint this wall, ADD to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, I must paint this wall, ADD to it! (Get task.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He sighs, then adds in a resigned t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sighs, then adds in a resigned tone: "If you must."

fields.Title: Backyard Wall: "There it is -- the most beautiful o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There it is -- the most beautiful of walls. Stop and admire it for a moment.
fields.Alternate1: The pastels of the wall seem still more luminous in the falling snow.
fields.Alternate2: Rain darkens the surface of the most beautiful of all walls, but does not in any way diminish its beauty.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim! I *must* paint this wall, add..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim! I *must* paint this wall, add even MORE beauty to it."

fields.Title: Backyard Wall: "This is a wall on the side of an ap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is a wall on the side of an apartment building.

fields.Title: Backyard Wall: "The wall waits mutely."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wall waits mutely.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Your hands shake as they reach for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your hands shake as they reach for the wall...

fields.Title: Logic: "Cindy the SKULL has all the necessa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cindy the SKULL has all the necessary materials. Talk to her?

fields.Title: Empathy: "He sounds tired of it all."
fields.Dialogue Text: He sounds tired of it all.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "Maybe this would be a good wall for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe this would be a good wall for dodge ball?

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Yes, do that. The wall will be wait..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, do that. The wall will be waiting.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""I'm sure I'll find the materials...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sure I'll find the materials. Then we can come back to this magnificent wall."

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "You have no clue. It's just a wall."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have no clue. It's just a wall.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Because -- you see it, finally -- t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because -- you see it, finally -- this wall is *sublime*! LOOK AT IT! The shadows, the colours...

fields.Title: You: "Look the wall over again, carefully..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look the wall over again, carefully. Think about what you could paint there...
fields.Alternate1: "I changed my mind. I *will* paint this wall."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I suppose we'll have to pass by it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I suppose we'll have to pass by it again at some point anyway," he says in a tone of resignation.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "All the other walls on all the othe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All the other walls on all the other houses must make a pilgrimage in adoration of this, the uncontested pinnacle of wall-craft. Colour peeled from the very face of god.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Blank, conveying nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Blank, conveying nothing.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Yeah, why? It's a wall, an ordinary..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, why? It's a wall, an ordinary wall.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Your loss. Farewell, snow-flecked w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your loss. Farewell, snow-flecked wall at the end of the world.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Your loss. Farewell, wall at the en..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your loss. Farewell, wall at the end of the world, draped in shadow.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["auto.is_raining"] == false  and  Variable["auto.is_snowing"] == false  and  IsNighttime()

fields.Title: You: "Cindy the SKULL has what I need."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cindy the SKULL has what I need.
fields.Alternate1: I already have heavy fuel oil, and Cindy the SKULL has a paintbrush...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Mhm, sure." The lieutenant looks u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm, sure." The lieutenant looks up at the wall reluctantly, then back at you.

fields.Title: You: "(Let the conceptual joy flow into y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Let the conceptual joy flow into your pupils and blossom into thoughts in your brain.)

fields.Title: You: ""I must talk to Cindy. Get the nece..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I must talk to Cindy. Get the necessary *materials* from her."
fields.Alternate1: "I already have the paint. Just need to get a paintbrush from Cindy the SKULL."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Yes, great thinking, go talk to her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, great thinking, go talk to her. The wall will be waiting.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Because this is no ordinary wall. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Because this is no ordinary wall. It is *sublime*! LOOK AT IT! The shadows, the colours...

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "You already have the heavy fuel oil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You already have the heavy fuel oil to use as paint -- it's red! -- and Cindy the SKULL has a paintbrush. This is on.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant sighs. "Why must we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant sighs. "Why must we stop to look at this wall every time we pass by? We have business to attend to."

fields.Title: You: "More!"
fields.Dialogue Text: More!

fields.Title: Backyard Wall: "Just an ordinary wall. Nothing to s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just an ordinary wall. Nothing to see here.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Huh?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Huh?"

fields.Title: You: "I'm sure I'll find them. And then I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm sure I'll find them. And then I'll return to this wall.

fields.Title: You: ""First, I know you're tired, Kim, b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "First, I know you're tired, Kim, but take another look at this wall. Draw *nourishment* from its beauty."

fields.Title: Logic: "Cindy the SKULL has a paintbrush an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cindy the SKULL has a paintbrush and paint. Talk to her.

fields.Title: Shivers: "So many walls all over Martinaise -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So many walls all over Martinaise -- weatherworn, cracked, their paint peeling...

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "O WALLFATHER!"
fields.Dialogue Text: O WALLFATHER!

fields.Title: You: "No. There is nothing to add to perf..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. There is nothing to add to perfection. (Back off.)

fields.Title: Logic: "You already have the heavy fuel oil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You already have the heavy fuel oil to use as paint, and Cindy the SKULL has a paintbrush. This is completely doable.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Absolutely. Now you just need the m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Absolutely. Now you just need the materials.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Your loss. Farewell, light-drenched..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your loss. Farewell, light-drenched wall at the end of the world.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Your loss. Farewell, rain-washed wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your loss. Farewell, rain-washed wall at the end of the world.
